CHANGELOG.md:183:- Added depth-2 coherence-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0065): `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` now ships a new `TestCoherenceEngineEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public `CoherenceEngine` and `NullCoherenceEngine` surface through complete end-to-end paths. The new tests walk every hook in canonical order (`pre_routing → post_routing → pre_lead → post_lead → pre_verify → post_verify → finalize`) and verify event types, phases, monotonic sequence numbers, run-id propagation, and SQLite persistence across an engine rebuild; write a `constitution.json` with one HARD and one SOFT keyword rule and confirm `EnforcementMode.FULL` blocks `post_routing`/`post_lead`/`post_verify` while `EnforcementMode.MONITOR` records the same violations without blocking, propagating HARD severity, both rule ids, and a negative trust delta on `post_lead`; record two architectural decisions through `record_decision` and confirm `pre_routing`/`pre_lead`/`pre_verify` inject the `## Active Decisions` block with at least one matching title; step the graduation manager across three `finalize` calls plus alternating `record_graduation_observation` outcomes and verify the run/observation/true-/false-positive counters and stable enforcement mode; round-trip a full replayed event payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys and verify each event's `sequence_number`, `run_id`, and dict `payload`; and loop `NullCoherenceEngine` across multiple run ids confirming every hook returns an approved verdict with empty violations and empty injected context plus an empty replay. `tests/test_test_coherence_engine_depth.py` pins `tests/test_coherence_engine.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestCoherenceEngine` and `TestNullCoherenceEngine` assertions and the production `promptclaw/coherence/engine.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4421 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
