CHANGELOG.md:187:- Added depth-2 cast-planner end-to-end test coverage (frac-0063): `tests/test_cast_planner.py` now ships a `TestCastPlannerEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public cast-planner surface (`select_cast_ids`, `assemble_cast`, plus the exported `CORE_ROLES` / `SUPPORT_ROLES` / `SAMPLER_METADATA_KEY` constants) through table-driven and looped end-to-end paths. The new tests sweep cast-history/energy combinations to confirm the canonical melody/rhythm/harmony lead with at least one support role across multiple support-role winners; sweep `(voice_count_target, max_chars, expected_size)` cases to verify clamping to `max_chars` and core-role ordering at every size; sweep preferred-synth palettes (`sw_bowed/sw_choir`, `sw_sampler/sw_bell`, `sw_drone/sw_recorder`) to confirm matching characters are promoted into the cast at `voice_count_target=5`; simulate a four-round cast-history rotation that pushes the most-recent support pick out of the next cast; drive multi-piece `assemble_cast` runs to verify piece-derived sampler-selector kwargs (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`) propagate correctly and the sampler summary is mirrored in both the assembled entry's `sample_record` and the metadata mapping; round-trip the assembled diagnostic payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys; and sweep selector outcomes (`sample`, `None`, `sample`) to verify `sampler_voice` always lands in the cast while `sampler_sample` metadata is attached only when the selector returns a sample. `tests/test_cast_planner_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `test_select_cast_*`, `test_voice_count_target_*`, `test_preferred_synths_*`, and `test_sampler_*` assertions are preserved unchanged; the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` source remains unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4409 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:189:- Added depth-2 capstone-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0062): `tests/test_capstone_engine.py` now includes `TestCapstoneCycleEndToEnd`, which drives the existing public `build_capstone_cycle()` API through complete EMSD capstone planning paths. The new tests verify all five canonical phases expose linked family, patch, arc, palette, mix, sampling, and DSP contracts; assert occupied Theramini routing activates the Conversation dialogue path and ducking behavior; assert away-practice late phases retarget sampling and DSP focus to `self_bus`; compare quiet cadences against occupied cycles for lower density and quieter mix targets; verify repertoire songs shape identity families, patches, imagery, and statement text; and round-trip phase diagnostics through `json.dumps`. `tests/test_capstone_engine_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 9 real functions versus 2 trivial). Existing capstone assertions and `my-claw/tools/senseweave/capstone_engine.py` source behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4401 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:191:- Added depth-2 breath-to-filter end-to-end test coverage (frac-0061): `tests/test_breath_to_filter.py` now ships a `TestBreathToFilterEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public breath-to-filter API (`estimate_breath_rate`, `breath_phase`, `breath_to_filter_params`, `breath_to_visual_params`) through complete synthetic listening paths. The new tests sweep multiple sine-breath BPMs (3, 6, 12) end-to-end through rate estimation, phase extraction, and filter/visual parameter derivation; assert the documented neutral output for flat and empty RMS histories; sweep a phase table (0.0–1.0) to verify cutoff peaks at inhale (0.25) and troughs at exhale (0.75), resonance peaks at extremes (0.0/0.5), and visual scale/brightness mirror the breath wave; check the documented `min(rate/15, 1.0)` mix-saturation curve across rate steps from 0 to 30 BPM; round-trip filter and visual outputs through `json.dumps`; render JSON-safe diagnostics across calm/fast/flat/noisy signal types; verify rate-detection tolerance per BPM, deterministic pipeline output, and a spot-check of the cosine cutoff curve at known phase extremes. `tests/test_breath_to_filter_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 26 real functions versus 24 trivial). Existing breath-to-filter assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/breath_to_filter.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (4392 tests, 3 skipped, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
