CHANGELOG.md:247:- Added depth-2 voice alias report helpers (frac-0032): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/voice_aliases.py` now exposes frozen `VoiceAliasEntry` and `VoiceAliasReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `voice_namespace`, `voice_alias_family`, `is_aliased_voice`, `iter_alias_pairs`, `aliases_for_target`, `alias_chain`, `build_voice_alias_entry`, `build_voice_alias_report`, and `summarize_voice_alias_report` so runtime/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing eleven-entry `RUNTIME_VOICE_ALIAS` table into a JSON-safe summary with ordered source/target voices, namespace counts (core vs senseweave), family counts (struck_tonal, metallic, granular, drum, other), senseweave-variant and core-alias counts, unique-target count, target-to-sources mapping, and per-alias entries flagging `is_senseweave_variant` and `is_changed`. Existing `resolve_runtime_voice_name` lookup behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_voice_aliases_depth.py` pins helper outputs, frozen entry/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with `resolve_runtime_voice_name`, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_voice_aliases.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
