CHANGELOG.md:265:- Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:267:- Added depth-2 sample-lab report helpers (frac-0022): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_lab.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplePlanReport` dataclass plus pure helpers `density_band`, `threshold_band`, `intensity_band`, `build_sample_plan_report`, and `summarize_sample_plan_report` so EMSD operator/diagnostics callers can resolve a `SamplePlan` together with its `sample_bank` freshness and fallback rule into one operator-readable view (source identity and capture path, refresh and freshness seconds, fallback list, cadence state, section function, transforms tuple plus count, density and named density band, buffer seconds, trigger threshold and named threshold band, intensity and named intensity band, and study focus) and emit a stable JSON-safe summary. Existing `SAMPLE_SOURCES`, `SAMPLE_SOURCE_ALIASES`, `SAMPLE_FALLBACKS`, `canonical_sample_source_name`, `sample_source`, `sample_bank`, and `plan_environmental_sampling` semantics are preserved (cadence and section-function shaping unchanged); `SamplePlan` now also carries the resolved `cadence_state` so reports can be built without re-passing it. `tests/test_sample_lab_depth.py` pins the band cutpoints, plan/bank field mirroring, alias-to-canonical bank resolution, section-function carry-through, JSON-safe summary shape, end-to-end downstream use, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sample_lab.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:271:- Added depth-2 silence budget report helpers (frac-0020): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/silence_budget.py` now exposes frozen `LaneSilenceBudgetStat` and `SilenceBudgetReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_silence_budget_stat`, `analyze_silence_budget`, and `summarize_silence_budget_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R10 rule once and inspect per-lane phrase outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, original phrase count, breath-extension count, tacet step count, distinct tacet phrase count, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TARGET_DENSITY`, `DEFAULT_THRESHOLD`, `SilenceBudgetRule.apply`, and `apply_silence_budget` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_silence_budget_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_silence_budget_depth.py` pins tacet-trigger lane shaping, breath-extension lane shaping, non-melodic non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:273:- Added depth-2 punctuation report helpers (frac-0019): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/punctuation.py` now exposes frozen `LanePunctuationStat` and `PunctuationReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lane_punctuation_stat`, `analyze_punctuation`, and `summarize_punctuation_report` so render diagnostics can apply the R6 punctuation rule once and inspect per-lane phrase-terminal outcomes (lane name, role, rendered step count, terminal-note count, extended-terminal count, inserted-breath count, mean terminal multiplier, mean breath milliseconds, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `DEFAULT_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `MAX_TERMINAL_MULTIPLIER`, `PunctuationRule.apply`, and `apply_punctuation` semantics are preserved so render-pipeline callers and `tests/test_punctuation_rule.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_punctuation_depth.py` pins melody shaping, non-melodic and lane-grid-locked non-application, scene/song/pattern aggregation, unsupported-score short-circuit, JSON-safe summary shape, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain startup identity regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:277:- Added depth-2 metric accent report helpers (frac-0017): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/metric_accent.py` now exposes frozen `LaneMetricAccentStat` and `MetricAccentReport` dataclasses plus `lane_metric_accent_stat`, `analyze_metric_accent`, and `summarize_metric_accent_report` so diagnostics can apply the R1 rule once and inspect per-lane shaping outcomes (lane name, role, meter, step count, shaped-step count, mean multiplier, strongest row, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `METRIC_ACCENT_4_4`, `metric_accent_table`, `MetricAccentRule.apply`, and `apply_metric_accent` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_metric_accent_depth.py` pins the new report surface and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_metric_accent_rule.py`, `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py`, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:281:- Added depth-2 render ablation helpers (frac-0015): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/ablation.py` now exposes frozen `AblationCase`, `AblationResult`, and `AblationSuite` dataclasses plus `rule_identifiers`, `build_ablation_cases`, `run_ablation_suite`, and `summarize_ablation_suite` so CCH-010 tooling can plan single-rule or custom ablation cases, render a full-stack baseline, execute each case through the existing `ablate()` seam, and return JSON-safe operator summaries with changed/unchanged counts. Existing `ablate()` behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_render_ablation.py` now pins suite planning, custom pair handling, summary output, and fractal depth >= 2, while debugger/listener-review and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:285:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:287:- Added depth-2 genre literacy helpers (frac-0012): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/genre_literacy.py` now exposes frozen `GenreSummary` / `GenreBlend` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_strategy`, `genre_compatibility`, `blend_genre_strategies`, and `recommend_genre_sequence` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can render a stable per-genre summary (label, tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, voice count, dominant grooves, top arc phases, calm/balanced/intense mood bucket), score a bounded `[0.0, 1.0]` symmetric compatibility between two traditions from arc-affinity cosine, modal/groove Jaccard ratios, and texture/chromatic distance, blend numeric hints with a clamped `[0.0, 1.0]` weight (tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, rubato tolerance, repetition tolerance, spatial width, sorted shared modal preferences), and plan one genre per supplied arc phase with rolling fatigue from prior selections. Existing `GenreStrategy`/`REQUIRED_GENRES` data, `strategy_for_genre`, `all_strategies`, `genre_arc_affinity`, `best_genres_for_phase`, and `select_genre` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_genre_literacy_depth.py` pins summary stability and mood bucketing, compatibility self-identity / symmetry / boundedness with related-vs-contrasted ranking, blend interpolation / clamp / modal intersection, sequence per-phase coverage with no immediate repeats, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:289:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:291:- Added depth-2 generation client_protocol helpers (frac-0010): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` now exposes a frozen `GenerationOutcome` dataclass plus pure helpers `cost_per_second`, `result_summary`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` so any backend (Replicate, Modal, local Ada, fakes) can compute USD-per-second cost from a `GenerationResult`, render a stable operator-readable summary dict (rounded duration / cost / per-second cost), emit a single-line `model=… dur=…s cost=$… latency=…ms id=…` log entry with `<unknown>` substituted for an empty `api_request_id`, and validate a result against its `GenerationRequest` (model match, sample-rate floor, duration tolerance, non-negative cost, non-negative latency) into a typed pass/fail outcome with stable reason ordering. The existing `GenerationResult` field order, `GenerationClient` Protocol contract, and downstream `client_replicate` / `client_modal` / `client_local` paths are preserved; `tests/test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins outcome shape, zero-duration cost handling, summary rounding, log-line ID fallback, and accumulated validation reasons, while existing client protocol, Replicate retry, Modal, local-Ada, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:293:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:295:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
CHANGELOG.md:305:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:313:- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity mutation endpoint (T-015@20260502T001347Z): `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` now accepts either a wrapped `{"mutations": [...]}` body or a single integration-spec `StateMutation` object, applies `set`, `increment`, `decrement`, `append`, and `remove` against entity `properties` paths, validates optional `target_entity` against the path ID, and persists the updated entity through duck-typed deploy-side store methods (`update_entity`/`patch_entity`/`save_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`record_entity`). The route returns the updated `EntityRecord`, surfaces missing entities as `404`, missing stores as `503`, validation failures as `422`, and downstream persistence failures as `502`. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the fighter `current_state` healthy-to-wounded round trip, numeric/list/nested mutation semantics, single-mutation payload compatibility, invalid-mutation no-persist behavior, missing entity/store handling, downstream failure handling, and shared-secret auth behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:315:- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity creation endpoint (T-014@20260502T001347Z): `POST /world/entities` now accepts `{type, name, domain, properties}`, validates `domain` against the `{shared, cypherclaw, deniable}` whitelist before touching the store, and routes through a new `create_world_entity(...)` helper that duck-types the deploy-side world store across `create_entity`/`add_entity`/`record_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`save_entity` (kwarg-shaped or single-mapping signatures). The route returns HTTP `201` with the store-assigned ID populated through the shared entity normalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable via `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`, falls back to the request input for `type`/`name`/`domain`/`properties` when the store returns a partial record, and surfaces HTTP `502` when the store returns no ID, `503` when no store can be constructed, and `422` for whitelist/empty-string violations. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the squad-member round trip via GET, each whitelisted domain, blank/missing-input rejection, downstream-failure handling, missing-store fallback, partial-record fallback, no-ID surfacing, the record-dict signature path, and shared-secret auth behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:317:- Added the CypherClaw narrative beat endpoint (T-011@20260502T001347Z): `POST /beats/next` now validates `{cycle_number, domain_filter, arc_position_target?, force_arc_event?}`, wraps an injected or lazily imported deploy-side `NarrativeEngine.next_beat()`, preserves the engine-owned serialized `StoryBeat` JSON shape without padding absent fields, and returns clear `503` unavailable / `502` generation-failure errors. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_beats.py` pins parameter passing, raw mapping shape preservation, dataclass/nested serialization, validation-before-engine behavior, downstream failure handling, missing-engine fallback, and shared-secret auth behavior.
CHANGELOG.md:319:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:321:- Added the CypherClaw narrative event append HTTP slice (T-003@20260502T001347Z): `POST /events` now accepts narrative events such as `raid.completed`, defaults omitted domains to `shared`, appends through the same injectable/lazy deploy-side event-store wrapper used by `GET /events`, normalizes the created event record, and returns downstream append failures as HTTP 502. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` pins raid-outcome persistence, read-after-write through `GET /events`, shared-domain defaults, validation, and downstream error handling.
CHANGELOG.md:323:- Added the CypherClaw narrative memory search HTTP slice (T-001@20260502T001347Z): new `cypherclaw.narrative_api` exposes `POST /memory/search` through a FastAPI `create_app(...)` factory, wraps deploy-side `NarrativeMemory` via lazy import, supports injected memory searchers for tests, normalizes common result shapes into ranked `{id, text, similarity, domain, metadata}` responses, and defensively honors `domain_filter` for shared/Deniable/CypherClaw memory separation. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` pins ranking, domain filtering, single-domain requests, validation, and downstream failure handling.
CHANGELOG.md:359:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:360:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
CHANGELOG.md:370:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
CHANGELOG.md:375:- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
CHANGELOG.md:378:- Added pre-performance self-critique and bounded revision passes: new `self_critique.py` module provides `preview_score()` for offline metric analysis, `critique_score()` for threshold-based quality gating, and `revise_score()` for one bounded rewrite attempt that preserves piece identity (key, mood, tempo) while improving at least one failed metric.
CHANGELOG.md:409:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
CHANGELOG.md:414:- Relaxed composer restart verification to the real steady-state condition: `restart_composer.sh` now waits for any healthy `duet_composer.py` process instead of only trusting the very first child PID, which avoids false failures during the current live startup race.
CHANGELOG.md:417:- Tightened the cold-boot wrapper to avoid daemon duplication: it now waits for `SuperCollider:out_1` before launching the meter, and it only backfills `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` if another startup source has not already brought them up during the same boot.
CHANGELOG.md:418:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
CHANGELOG.md:432:- Made the sampler musically scene-aware instead of only transform-aware: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits scene profiles like `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, and `afterglow_residue`, and `sample_event_renderer.py` now changes duration, density, peak target, filtering, stretch, and echo geometry from those profiles so the room layer follows the tracker form instead of using one generic behavior under different labels.
CHANGELOG.md:440:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
CHANGELOG.md:442:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
CHANGELOG.md:443:- Built the first end-to-end EMSD package: added a 40-course curriculum catalog plus generated `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*` scaffolds, and implemented `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py` so the electronic music production roadmap now exists as runnable code and tests instead of only a brief.
CHANGELOG.md:449:- Made face captions harmonic-function-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now uses `cadence_type` for `Resolution` and `Afterglow`, so the same hook can resolve differently under dominant, plagal, authentic, and deceptive harmonic landings.
CHANGELOG.md:451:- Made scene captions section-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now reshapes the same hook differently for `Theme`, `Recap`/`Release`, and `Resolution`/`Afterglow`, so face text follows the song arc instead of repeating one caption verbatim.
CHANGELOG.md:459:- Broke the fixed tracker-song mold: `tracker_form_for_family(..., song_num=...)` now yields variant forms with different scene counts and scene-length multipliers, so CypherClaw no longer plays every song with the same five-scene duration profile.
CHANGELOG.md:475:- Added explicit runtime voice aliases so unavailable or unsafe voices can degrade cleanly: `grain` now resolves to `breath`, and `tabla_ge` currently resolves to `tabla_tin` until a real `sw_tabla_ge` SynthDef is deployed.
CHANGELOG.md:479:- Added a concrete CypherClaw upgrade checklist covering phase status, owned files, test gates, and live deployment order for the presence/cadence/personality/audio-efficiency program.
CHANGELOG.md:495:- Taught Telegram `/prd` to load stage order from `sdp/execution-roadmap.md` and batch mappings from `sdp/execution-roadmap.queue-map.json`, so roadmap output follows the current clone/identity/embodiment/publication plan instead of a stale hardcoded stage list.
CHANGELOG.md:523:- Added Decision Store for Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) with keyword-based retrieval.
CHANGELOG.md:543:- Added an interactive startup wizard that asks onboarding questions one at a time.
CHANGELOG.md:544:- Added heuristic follow-up questions when startup answers are vague or underspecified.
CHANGELOG.md:546:- Added startup artifacts: `docs/STARTUP_PROFILE.md`, `docs/STARTUP_TRANSCRIPT.md`, and `.promptclaw/onboarding/startup-session.md`.
CHANGELOG.md:547:- Added agent roster customization and capability inference during startup.
