CHANGELOG.md:364:- Added listener-review workflow: `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` documents weekly review cadence, step-by-step rule ablation via the `senseweave-render-debugger` CLI (CCH-010), and how to attach review notes; `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` provides a structured template with piece, date, felt_wrong, suspected_rule, ablation_result, and action fields; `render.listener_review` validates artifact integrity and anchors the documented CLI name to the live debugger parser.
CHANGELOG.md:368:- Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to "unavailable" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.
CHANGELOG.md:379:- Tuned local SDP agent templates for dirty-baseline operation: leads must commit task-scoped changes, while verifiers now treat unrelated pre-existing dirty workspace state as notes instead of failing otherwise-correct tasks or asking agents to clean another operator's work.
CHANGELOG.md:382:- Fixed the long-section tracker compile bug that was turning songs into isolated sustained tones: `tracker_compiler.py` now converts large section budgets into repeat counts plus modest note-length scaling, and `music_tracker.py` quantizes those repeats into real repeated phrase cycles instead of stretching a handful of notes across the whole scene.
CHANGELOG.md:441:- Fed EMSD production plans into actual tracker playback: added `emsd_performance.py`, wired `duet_composer.py` to apply live mix/sample/DSP adjustments at the note boundary, extended `composer_emsd_extras()` with concrete sample capture metadata, and made the strongest top register fold down harder so notes above roughly `C6` are lowered an octave and the sharpest band is lowered two octaves.
CHANGELOG.md:446:- Very high-note playback shaping is now stronger and more explicit: `voice_shaping.py` emits best-effort `highpass_hz` and `saturation_mix` controls in addition to the existing top-octave gain/brightness/release shaping, and `play_voice()` forwards those controls so ear-splitting notes can be filtered and driven slightly when the live SynthDefs support it.
CHANGELOG.md:460:- Added a small high-note saturation-style shaping layer for live playback. Because the current synths do not expose a true drive parameter, very high notes are softened by trimming gain/release, reducing pluck brightness, and adding a little detune/space instead of sending unsupported OSC args.
